SUMMARY:TDOV: "What's Tea"
DESCRIPTION:Calling in all BIPOC trans femmes & Trans People to come eat\, breathe & let your hair down in solidarity for our Annual TDOV “What’s Tea” \nThough this is a space catering to our Queer/Trans Folks All from the community are welcome. This gathering is a partnership between The LGBTQ Center of Durham\, Southerners On New Ground (SONG)\, Black LGBTQ Migrant Project (BLMP)\, and The Transgender Law Center (TLC)
URL:https://durhamcentralpark.org/upcoming-event/tdov-whats-tea/
LOCATION:The Pavilion\, 501 Foster Street\, Durham\, NC\, 27701\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://durhamcentralpark.org/content/uploads/TDOV26-Official-FLYER.jpg
END:VEVENT
